        "issue": {
          "active_lock_reason": null,
          "assignee": null,
          "assignees": [],
          "author_association": "MEMBER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\nReport: `docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\nFinding: #26\n\nMoved from mistakenly filed meta issue: ConcaveTrillion/ocr-container-meta#319\n\nEvidence:\n\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/adapters/pp_doclayout.py:70`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/adapters/pp_doclayout.py:85`\n- `pd_book_tools/layout/adapters/pp_doclayout.py:86`\n\n`checkpoint_path` can be a local directory or Hugging Face repo ID and is passed directly to `from_pretrained()`. `trust_remote_code` is not enabled, which helps, but model/config/artifact loading remains a trust and resource boundary.\n\nImpact:\n\n- External callers exposing this parameter can let users load large or maliciously shaped models.\n\nRemediation:\n\n- Document the trust boundary.\n- Require explicit opt-in for remote custom repos.\n- Support allowlists/pinned revisions and high-security `local_files_only=True` modes.\n- Enforce artifact-size limits where practical.\n\n---\nThis issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-25T03:22:13Z",
